<br>
Back:  Cloak of the Maelstrom (11ac, 3str, 10dex, 6sta, 5int, 55hp)<br>
Arms:  Hardened Grey Flesh Sleeves (16ac, 6str/dex/sta, 25hp)<br>
Feet:  Barbed Dragonscale Boots (19ac, 9sta, 30hp)<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=339348"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.seretogis.org/files/linkables/garzok - overlord sig.png" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=enchantingwasubi>EnchantingWasubi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/11/03 5:22:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4833.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   expensive on mine</span><hr size=1> ok the boots go to 10k, the sleeves go for 5k and the cloak I think it is also 5k.  That is on tunare so the stuff is expensive.  Frostbringer is 10k and I seen a SOD for a cool million and one for 340k.  SO i will try to get that stuff my warrior is in trader mode now and hopefully the cheap bastards on my server would by something <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roughbeard>Roughbeard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/11/03 5:56:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4833.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: expensive on mine</span><hr size=1> Dont swap out ac for hp/sta too early... get a healty balance between.. who cares if you have high unbuffed hp if you only have 1k in ac.. if you are only avoiding 30% of blows but have higher unbuffed hp vs someone who is avoiding 60% of blows but lower hp (random numbers pulld out of my arse) who is going to need more healing? <br>
but if you really want to:<br>
Ditch the Couger Claws, get 2 Orc Fangs, you would lose 4 dex and gain 30hp. <br>
Thurg MQs for all pieces but helm legs and bp are ~1k each and dropping, dont know about your server but they were all ~1k before i quit. <br>
Draconic Pauldrons (quested) or Chokdai Hide Pauldrons or Matchless Dragonwing Mantle or Barbed Dragonscale Pauldrons, barbed would be your best bet if you cant quest the draconic since the Chokdai have -10str but +55hp, Matchless would be too expensive for shoulders<br>
Cloak of Maelstrom or Heirophant Cloak would be for Hps/sta on back<br>
Ditch the CC Gloves, get some +hp Gloves.. lots out there, (SS(+90)/Thurg(+40) MQ would be best)<br>
Clattering Bone Necklace for Neck<br>
Potc earring<br>
90hp ring<br>
<br>
With those you would lose a decent amount of ac, but would gain hps, its your choice <p>Rough <br>
